prepare for release

none

The "wdm" program, branch 1.27.

The "wdm" program, branch 1.27.

patch by Thomas Glanzmann

I don't think those changes was necessary, but if they make someone's life little better, why not apply it? :) It is said, that without these, wdm didn't work correctly on sunray servers

fix pam_open_session

"I'm running wdm-1.27 on FreeBSD 5.2-CURRENT. Since version 1.26, PAM code seems not to work. ( This means that ssh-agent is not started even if pam_ssh.so is enabled. )

I have checked src/wdm/session.c. If system has setusercontext(), I guess that pam_open_session() will never be called." Reported by Kan Sasaki <sasaki@fcc.ad.jp>

update aa code

Antialiasing API has chaged in new wmaker. I need to update code. New code uses some #ifdefs. They should go away soon.

update config

config file for aegis needs to be updated because create_symlinks_before_build field is obsolete. I need to use development_directory_style.source_file_symlink field.

fix fd leak - II

Last descriptor leaked si return value of mkstemp function. I'm totally forgot, that this function returns value. Thanks Michael Gernoth for reminding me about it. :)

fix fd leak - I

wdm leaks file descriptors to child processes. That's bad. This change fixed all leaked pipes and file descriptor for log. The only one left is leaked descriptor for removed auth file

Welsh translation

Welsh translation sent to me by Kevin Donnelly <kevin@dotmon.com>

problem with xdmcp and ipv6

Jennifer Elaan <jen@elaan.com> reported "that wdm drops the connection to the X server after login but before running Xsession.". Later she mailed me with "My partner just isolated and corrected this problem. The culprit is bad handling of IPv6 packets, which triggers a debug message with invalid arguments."

fix AUTHORS

add latest translators and contributors to AUTHORS file.

The "wdm" program, branch 1.26.

The "wdm" program, branch 1.26.

prepare for release

update NEWS

fix warning on FreeBSD

found another warning while compiling on FreeBSD. "src/wdm/util.c:139: warning: implicit declaration of function `sigsetmask'." I don't see that on Linux.

I simplified part dealing with signals. The setpgrp function differs on FreeBSD and Linux, but setpgid is not. I tested everything at least to compile on Linux and FreeBSD. I hope it will work on other BSD systems as well.

remove ExitLogin

ExitLogin is generally not needed. There is new option to configure --enable-exitlogin for those who wants it.

make clean

make clean target should remove everything that can be rebuild wiht simple make. including generated config files.

fix text in INSTALL file

Section 4 about make clean and make distclean is not correct. Also name of configs directory should be fixed (it refers to ./config).

typo in configure help

it displays BLACLBOX_PATH instead of BLACKBOX_PATH

warnings in src/wdm/resource.c

src/wdm/resource.c cannot be recompiled with gcc-3.3.2 because of warnings: "src/wdm/resource.c:231: warning: dereferencing type-punned pointer will break strict-aliasing rules".

Everything that raised that warning was converted to union. I hope nothing is broken.

FreeBSD compatibility - III

don't use -D flag of install which is GNU specific and is not available in BSD install. reported by Geir Ove Myhr <myhr+wdm@fysmat.ntnu.no>

obsolete header

remove inclusion of <malloc.h> it is obsolete and should be replaced with <stdlib.h>. reported by Geir Ove Myhr <myhr+wdm@fysmat.ntnu.no>

i18n

Don't call gettext (directly) in wdmLogin if I18N is not defined. reported by Geir Ove Myhr <myhr+wdm@fysmat.ntnu.no>

FreeBSD compatibility - II

remove wrong prototypes for setgrent etc. reported by Geir Ove Myhr <myhr+wdm@fysmat.ntnu.no>

FreeBSD compatibility

include <signal.h> into loghelpers.c explicitly. reported by Geir Ove Myhr <myhr+wdm@fysmat.ntnu.no>

wdm - SELinux support

SELinux support added by Tom Vogt <tom@lemuria.org>

french translation

added french translation by Mathieu Roy <yeupou@gnu.org>

fix debug compilation

there's some calls to Debug left, can be reproduced with --enable-debug option specified to configure (reported by vlaad). I removed offending code, because it's not used anywhere.

prepare for release
